# One-agent-per-feature workflow

Each session implements **one** backlog feature, scoped by a feature spec. Full
process, acceptance-criteria patterns, and branch naming:
`docs/specs/features/README.md` (AF-8). Git/PR policy: ADR-0005.

- **One feature, one branch, one PR.** Branch `feat/<backlog-id>-<slug>`; never push
  to `main`. Reference the backlog ID in commits and the PR.
- **Scaffold the scope doc first.** Run `pnpm gen:create-feature-spec` (skill:
  `create-feature-spec`) — writes `docs/specs/features/<slug>.md` only. The agent
  workflow toolkit does **not** prescribe project code layout (ADR-0006).
- **The feature spec is the contract.** Fill goal, acceptance criteria (gate /
  structural / behavioral prefixes), touched modules, out of scope. Check boxes
  (`- [x]`) as you complete them; all must pass before opening the PR.
- **Gates are non-negotiable.** `pnpm lint`, `typecheck`, `test`, and `doc-lint`
  (when docs changed) must pass — see the **gate:** criteria in the spec template.
- **Status lifecycle:** `Draft` → `Active` (implementation started) → `Completed`
  (merged). Set `Completed` when the owner merges; mark the backlog item done.
- **Session closeout.** End with a detailed summary (goal, changes, gates, remaining
  work). Ask the owner for permission before commit, push, or PR — see `AGENTS.md`
  § End of session and `.cursor/rules/git-workflow.mdc`.

Structural criteria reference **this project's** architecture, not a toolkit default.
